    56	- For comparison, `keeper-vault.v1` is `supported`, with evidence at `docs/live-proof/keeper-vault.v1.91119c4.sanitized.json` and `since_pin` `91119c4e4f08139eec810ea6550abf92f8e79240` (`keeper_sdk/core/schemas/keeper-vault/keeper-vault.v1.schema.json:6`).
    57	- Vault’s evidence chain validates `validate -> plan -> apply -> discover -> verify -> re-plan -> destroy plan -> destroy apply -> re-discover` (`docs/live-proof/keeper-vault.v1.91119c4.sanitized.json:14`).
    58	- Typed model coverage for sharing is all four blocks: `SharingManifestV1` has `folders`, `shared_folders`, `share_records`, and `share_folders` fields (`keeper_sdk/core/sharing_models.py:172`).
    59	- The `share_folders` model uses `kind` as the discriminator across `grantee`, `record`, and `default` variants (`keeper_sdk/core/sharing_models.py:150`).
    60	- Current diff coverage is **folders only**. The docstring says sibling blocks are deferred, and the public function enforces that with `NotImplementedError` (`keeper_sdk/core/sharing_diff.py:1`, `keeper_sdk/core/sharing_diff.py:340`).
    61	- Current folder diff tests cover 12 folder-only cases; the only future-block test asserts `NotImplementedError` (`tests/test_sharing_diff_folders.py:72`, `tests/test_sharing_diff_folders.py:180`).
