    63	- Commander provider has sharing-adjacent scaffold helpers only: `_ensure_folder_exists` calls `mkdir -uf`; `_ensure_shared_folder_exists` calls `mkdir -sf`; `_share_folder_to_ksm_app` calls `secrets-manager share add` (`keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:1292`, `keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:1298`, `keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:1314`).
    64	- The provider does not currently call `share-record` or `share-folder`; its documented command list covers PAM/vault commands and omits those share verbs (`keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:9`).
    65	- CLI plan/apply dispatch is not wired for sharing: `load_declarative_manifest` supports PAM and vault only, and rejects other valid families (`keeper_sdk/core/manifest.py:88`, `keeper_sdk/core/manifest.py:129`).
    66	- The CLI `_build_plan` branch is likewise PAM-or-vault only (`keeper_sdk/cli/main.py:693`, `keeper_sdk/cli/main.py:706`).
